The paper deals with optimization in wireless communication networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on stochastic processes and the use of stochastic differential equations (SDEs) suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of wireless networks and cross-layer optimization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques and the focus on convergence analysis suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.MA) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
